name: Bioactive Compound Library
description: A collection of 4548 bioactive compounds for HTS and HCS, consists of inhibitors, agonists and natural products, over 350 targets distributed in fields of cancer, cardiovascular disease, metabolic disease, neurological disease, infection, inflammation, immunology, endocrinology and so on.

name: FDA-approved Compound Library
description: A collection of 2070 marketed drugs for HTS and HCS, over 200 targets, covered fields in cancer, cardiovascular disease, metabolic disease, neurological disease, infection, etc.

name: Kinase Inhibitor Library
description: A collection of 637 compounds for HTS and HCS, targeting over 80 kinases, such as tyrosine kinase receptors, protein kinases, lipid kinases, etc.

name: Tyrosine Kinase Library
description: A collection of 377 compounds for HTS and HCS, used to research related diseases and drug screening, targeted over 30 tyrosine kinase targets, such as VEGFR, EGFR, FGFR, etc.

name: Natural Product Library
description: A collection of 1284 natural products for HTS and HCS, isolated from plants or biological separation, contains Quinones, Flavonoids, Terpenoids, Glycosides, Steroids, Alkaloid, Phenols and Saccharides.

name: Anti-virus Compound Library
description: A collection of 249 anti-virus compounds for HTS and HCS and a useful tool for the discovery of anti-virus drugs, targeting at HIV, HBV, HCV, HSV, RSV, CMV, CoV, Influenza Virus, etc.

name: Neurodegenerative Diseases Compound Library
description: A collection of 516 drugs for HTS and HCS, which are used to treat 18 kinds of different neurodegenerative diseases in clinical studies, such as Alzheimer, Parkinson, Dementia with Lewy bodies, Multiple system atrophy, Huntington's disease, etc.

name: Epigenetics Compound Library
description: A collection of 311 compounds for HTS and HCS, targeting on proteins involved in Epigenetics pathways, most of which can regulate methylation or acetylation modification.

name: Autophagy Compound Library
description: A collection of 688 compounds for HTS and HCS, targeting on proteins related with autophagy, including mTOR, PI3K, ULK, etc.

name: Cell Cycle Compound Library
description: A collection of 296 compounds for HTS and HCS, targeting on proteins related in cell cycle pathway.

name: Apoptosis Compound Library
description: A collection of 579 compounds for HTS and HCS, targeting on proteins related in apoptosis pathways, such as PARP, Bcl-2, p53, MDM2, FAK, caspase, etc.

name: Anti-cancer Compound Library
description: A collection of 1847 compounds reported in cancer research articles, covering multiple cancers.

name: Human Endogenous Metabolite Compound Library
description: The Endogenous Metabolite Compound Library contains 295 human endogenous metabolites, including amino acids, organic acids, nucleic acids, fatty acids, amines, sugars, vitamins, cofactors, cancer metabolite.

name: GPCR Protein Compound Library
description: A unique collection of 668 compounds targeting G protein coupled receptors used in GPCR screening for various research and drug development projects.

name: Histone Modification Compound Library
description: A unique collection of 185 compounds targeting histone modification, such as Epigenetic Reader Domain, HDAC, Histone Acetyltransferase, etc, for high throughput screening (HTS) and high content screening (HCS).

name: Small Molecule Immuno-Oncology Compound Library
description: A unique collection of 126 bioactive tumor immunology compounds targeting on PD-1/PD-L1, IDO, CCR, CXCR, TLR, STAT3, etc, for high throughput screening (HTS) and high content screening (HCS).

name: Differentiation Inducing Compound Library
description: A unique collection of 391 cell differentiation-inducing compounds for high throughput screening (HTS) and high content screening (HCS), cancer stem cells, neural stem cells, cardiomyocyte stem cells, osteogenic stem cells are included.

name: Immunology/Inflammation Compound Library
description: A unique collection of 361 compounds with biological activity used for Immunology/Inflammation research and related assays, targeting on COX, IL Receptor, Histamine Receptor, ROS, etc.

name: Ubiquitination?Compound?Library
description: A unique collection of 138 compounds with biological activity used for Ubiquitination related research and for high throughput screening (HTS) and high content screening (HCS), targeting on Proteasome, DUB, E3 Ligase, E1 Activating, E2 conjugating, etc.

name: Anti-alzheimer Disease Compound Library
description: Anti-alzheimer's Disease Compound Library contains 395 alzheimer-related compounds for screening effective drugs for alzheimer treatment.

name: CNS-penetrant Compound Library
description: CNS-penetrant Compound Library contains 319 CNS-Penetrant compounds with biological activity for neurologic research and associated assays. Targets include AChR, 5-HT Receptor, Dopamine Receptor, etc.

name: Anti-coronavirus Compound Library
description: A collection of 45 anti-coronavirus compounds for HTS and HCS and a useful tool for the discovery of anti- CoVID-19 drugs, targeting at SARS-CoV, MERS-CoV, etc.

name: Clinical Compound Library
description: A collection of 2260 clinical compounds for HTS and HCS.
